Like, most of my act is just,

55:07.137 --> 55:08.137
you know...

55:08.222 --> 55:09.222
uh...

55:09.306 --> 55:11.846
gossip and... and trickery.

55:13.644 --> 55:16.614
Do you know what I mean?
Like some cheap magician, you know?

55:19.566 --> 55:22.026
So, I'll tell you the only thing
I know for a fact,

55:22.110 --> 55:23.860
and it's something that we all know.

55:23.946 --> 55:25.316
Everybody knows it,

55:25.405 --> 55:27.945
but it's harder to act on it, it is.

55:28.033 --> 55:31.703
But the only really true thing

55:31.787 --> 55:33.407
is that...

55:33.956 --> 55:38.126
we all must love each other.

55:41.255 --> 55:43.715
And it's very difficult, you know?

55:43.799 --> 55:45.429
It's very, very hard.

55:46.593 --> 55:47.803
Hey, what about this?

55:47.886 --> 55:49.846
A dog loves people.

55:49.930 --> 55:53.560
Like, you think it's hard to love people -
a dog loves everybody.

55:53.642 --> 55:54.982
Like, a dog...

55:55.852 --> 55:58.062
Like, my dog, right,

55:58.146 --> 55:59.476
I've never seen such a...

55:59.565 --> 56:00.565
No judgement.

56:00.649 --> 56:02.779
Like, my dog, all he does is love me.

56:02.859 --> 56:03.859
When I wake up...

56:03.944 --> 56:05.454
I think he watches me sleeping,

56:05.529 --> 56:07.529
because when I wake up, he's right there,

56:07.614 --> 56:08.994
and he's like, "I love you!"

56:09.074 --> 56:11.244
He jumps up. He's licking my face.

56:11.326 --> 56:13.996
"I love you more than anything!
You're the greatest!"

56:14.079 --> 56:16.619
I go, "Thanks.
You're cool, too. I love you."

56:16.707 --> 56:19.167
"I love you more than anything!"
"I love you, too."

56:19.251 --> 56:21.171
"Remember yesterday
when you threw that bone

56:21.253 --> 56:22.813
and it turned out to be a rubber bone?"

56:22.838 --> 56:25.668
"Yeah, it was a joke.
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings."

56:25.757 --> 56:28.677
"I wasn't! I wasn't!
I was laughing. It was funny."

56:29.261 --> 56:31.891
"Oh, you love me so much, and I love you."

56:31.972 --> 56:33.352
This is the greatest thing.

56:33.432 --> 56:35.772
"I'm just going to kiss you
and kiss you forever."

56:35.851 --> 56:38.561
I go, "Yes, you can do that."
"I'm just going to keep kissing you."

56:38.645 --> 56:40.855
Then I go, "OK,
get the fuck away from me, all right?!"

56:42.316 --> 56:43.936
"Just leave me alone, would you?"

56:46.278 --> 56:49.408
"I've got to write shit
into a magic phone and stuff."

56:49.489 --> 56:51.199
I've got no time for this...

56:51.825 --> 56:53.615
"fucking dog stuff."

56:57.247 --> 56:58.957
Then my dog goes, "You're right."

57:02.919 --> 57:04.499
"I find... You know, I love you,

57:04.588 --> 57:07.758
but I... I just push too hard."

57:10.177 --> 57:12.007
"I push and I push and I push,

57:12.095 --> 57:13.595
and I push you away."

57:16.642 --> 57:17.982
"I'm no good."

57:18.727 --> 57:20.517
"I'm no damn good."

57:26.234 --> 57:27.324
"But what say..."

57:28.195 --> 57:31.155
what say I just stood here

57:31.239 --> 57:32.659
and stared at you...

57:35.577 --> 57:37.157
Completely quietly...

57:38.038 --> 57:40.458
until, finally, you looked at me again...

57:41.166 --> 57:42.246
with some look of love,

57:42.334 --> 57:44.254
"and then I jump up and love you again?"

57:46.505 --> 57:49.005
And you go, "Yes, that would be fine."

57:50.217 --> 57:51.297
"Do that."

57:56.348 --> 57:57.848
They don't judge, dogs.

57:57.933 --> 58:01.943
We judge, you know?
All our love comes with caveats, you know?

58:02.020 --> 58:05.980
There's no such thing
as unconditional love with human beings.

58:06.066 --> 58:08.106
But dogs, they don't care.

58:08.193 --> 58:09.193
They love...

58:09.277 --> 58:11.237
Hitler had a dog. Now, you think of that.

58:13.657 --> 58:15.367
I'm no fan of Hitler.

58:17.035 --> 58:18.075
I never liked him.

58:19.663 --> 58:23.633
I didn't like him
before it was cool not to like him.

58:26.878 --> 58:31.678
But there was a dog in history
who loved Hitler more than anyone.

58:31.758 --> 58:33.588
He would wake up in the morning and go,

58:33.677 --> 58:34.757
"Where's Hitler?!"

58:34.845 --> 58:35.845
You know?

58:37.222 --> 58:39.272
And Göring, or somebody, would go,

58:39.349 --> 58:41.639
"He's not here.
He's doing some evil stuff."

58:43.145 --> 58:46.015
"I've explained to you, he spends
most of his time doing evil stuff.

58:46.106 --> 58:47.686
You can't see him that often."

58:47.774 --> 58:49.154
He goes, "OK. Yeah, I know."

58:49.234 --> 58:52.704
I'm not trying to...
Listen, Göring, I love you, you know?

58:52.779 --> 58:56.279
I love Mengele, I love everybody.
All you guys are the greatest.

58:56.366 --> 59:00.616
"But it's just Hitler
is the greatest man who's ever lived."

59:10.464 --> 59:14.384
This is why we ask
that you don't use recording devices.

59:25.520 --> 59:26.520
Just...

59:26.605 --> 59:30.315
I don't want to be with fucking
Harvey Levin tomorrow or something.

59:32.986 --> 59:36.656
"Did you say Hitler was the greatest?"
And what would be my fucking answer?

59:36.740 --> 59:38.580
I would go, "No, it was a dog."

59:41.161 --> 59:43.161
That wouldn't work. I would be fucked.

59:48.001 --> 59:49.001
But...

59:49.503 --> 59:54.173
I'll be goddamned if I'm going
to end a special talking about Hitler.

59:58.929 --> 01:00:00.969
Yeah, that's what I'm going to do -

01:00:01.056 --> 01:00:02.386
end a special...

01:00:03.517 --> 01:00:07.147
I'm going to call my special <i>Hitler's Dog.</i>

